.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\f(CR<addr>:<port>\fP
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\f(CRhttp://<addr>:<port>\fP
.RE
.sp
It is recommended to use the couchbase://<addr> format for standard
installations. The other two formats allow an option to take a port number which
is needed for non\-default installations where the admin port has been set up on
a port other that 8091.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
To enable node\-to\-node encryption in a cluster with two host
\f(CR[cb1.mydomain.com:8091, cb2.mydomain.com:8091]\fP ran the following
commands:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ couchbase\-cli node\-to\-node\-encryption \-c cb1.mydomain.com:8091 \-\-username Administrator \(rs
 \-\-password password \-\-enable
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
To check if node\-to\-node encryption is on or off ran:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ couchbase\-cli node\-to\-node\-encryption \-c cb1.mydomain.com:8091 \-\-username Administrator \(rs
  \-\-password password \-\-get
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
To disable node\-to\-node encryption use the following command:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ couchbase\-cli node\-to\-node\-encryption \-c cb1.mydomain.com:8091 \-\-username Administrator \(rs
\-\-password password \-\-disable
.fi
.if n .RE
